<HEADLINE> Vietnam Hopes for Stability in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam sincerely hopes the
Indonesian people will soon restore stability and continue making
their country prosperous, a spokesperson for Vietnam Foreign
Ministry said on saturday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam is following the situation in Indonesia with close
attention, the spokesperson said.
</P>
<P>
All the member countries of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) have taken different measures to help Indonesia
overcome difficulties, and to maintain stability in the region,
said the spokesperson.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese Embassy in Indonesia is now in normal operation,
the spokesperson added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
