<HEADLINE> India Offers to Discuss Nuclear Issue With Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 16 (Xinhua) -- India is ready and willing to
discuss the nuclear issue with neighboring Pakistan anytime,
Brajesh Mishra, principal secretary to Prime Minister Atal Bihari
Vajpayee, said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"We do not want to dominate any other nation, nor do we want to
attack anyone, but we must have a deterrent so that no one should
dare to attack us," Mishra said on the local Star TV.
</P>
<P>
When asked whether India would consider offering no-first-use
option to Pakistan, he said he had no idea whether Islamabad is
also ready to discuss the nuclear issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
