<HEADLINE> HKSAR Wins Again in Pacific Rim Rugby Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Last year's runner-up Hong Kong,
China, won the second match on home turf in the 1998 Pacific Rim
Rugby Championship by beating the U.S. team 43-25 here on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Last weekend, the home side won over Canada 23-17 in the first
of the three-match set to be played in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
In a demonstration match earlier on Saturday, China's national
team trounced Hong Kong Dragons 67-3. The local team had several
mainstay players missing as a Hong Kong sevens team is in France
for an international tournament.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, China, is to meet Japan here next weekend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
