<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Palestinians Injured in Hebron's Clashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, May 16 (Xinhua) -- At least three Palestinians were
injured in clashes Saturday in Hebron and five others arrested in
the Old City of East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
In Hebron, which is situated in the south of the West Bank,
hundreds of Palestinians took to the street in the center of the
city where Jewish settlers live and clashed with Israeli
troops there, according to the Jerusalem Media and Communication
Center (JMCC).
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians threw stones at the Israeli soldiers, who
returned fire with rubber bullets.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli soldiers forced the store keepers to close their
shops in the city and stormed a company near Bab-Ezzawyeh, the
JMCC said.
</P>
<P>
The injured included a child who was taken to hospital after
being shot in the head.
</P>
<P>
Confrontations between Palestinians and Israeli security forces
took place Saturday at Salah Eddine Street in East Jerusalem,
where most of the residents are Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians asked the Israeli side to release five
Palestinians who were arrested during Thursday's demonstrations
before the confrontations took place.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians also threw stones at a nearby Israeli police
station and five of them were arrested by the Israeli police.
</P>
<P>
Palestinians held a "Million people march" on Thursday to mark
the 50th anniversary of Nakba (catastrophe), the Palestinian's
designation of the founding of the State of Israel and subsequent
dispersion of the Palestinian people.
</P>
<P>
At least nine Palestinians were reportedly killed by
Israeli troops Thursday when angry Palestinians clashed with
Israeli forces, leaving another bitter memory of hatred among
the Palestinians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
