<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SADC Culture Meeting Opens in Harare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 16 (Xinhua) -- A week-long session of the Southern
African Development Community (SADC) experts meeting started here
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, aimed at finding ways and means through which the
various member countries can invest in culture, will center on
information, sport and culture with a view to solve the common
problems that affect the countries in the region.
</P>
<P>
Participants will also discuss the flow of information in the
region, including copyright and cultural information systems.
</P>
<P>
Officially opening the meeting, Zimbabwe's Deputy Minister of
Education, Sports and Culture, Kembo Mohadi, said it is important
to create a regional cultural and information network as an
efficient policy to design, implement and evaluate cultural
development and to strengthen indigenous culture.
</P>
<P>
He urged countries in the region to ensure a better
integration of the cultural dimension of development strategies
and programs.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which draws more than 60 delegates from the SADC
countries, will also discuss problems facing the various sporting
disciplines in the region, including financing and racism.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
