<DOCNO> XIE19980517.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-16 18:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait to Call for Saudi, Omani Membership in WTO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Minister of Commerce
and Industry Abdelaziz Al-Dekheel said on Saturday Kuwait would
call for the membership of Saudi Arabia and Oman in the World
Trade Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks before leaving for Geneva to attend
the WTO's second ministerial meeting.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the meeting, Kuwait would call for the
adoption of recommendations that would facilitate the admission of
developing countries to the WTO.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia, a heavyweight in the Arab world and the
Gulf region, and Oman have been trying to join the world
multilateral trade organization for the past several years.
</P>
<P>
Al-Dekheel said Kuwait would support all efforts aimed at
bringing success for the new world trade order, believing that
this was the only way to achieve comprehensive development in the
developing and under-developing countries.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the importance of international cooperation
in the trade field. 
