<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Speaker Commends China's Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Dawit Yohannes, Speaker of
Ethiopia's House of People's Representatives, Saturday commended
China's experience in the field of human rights as most
successful and significant.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks during a meeting with Zeng Jianhui,
Chairman of the Foreign Affairs Committee of China's National
People's Congress, who arrived here Saturday morning to attend a
five-day International Conference on Human Rights and Ombudsman
to be opened here next Monday.
</P>
<P>
Yohannes said, China's conception of human rights is widely
representative in the developing countries, and is worth learning
by developing countries including Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
According to the speaker, the right to survival is the most
critical. Ethiopia, Yohannes said, while focusing on nation
building and poverty eradication, is fully devoted to the full
realization of the basic of human rights.
</P>
<P>
The western way of approaching human rights issue, with its
emphasis on individuals, is meaningless for developing countries
such as Ethiopia, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia and China have many similarities in the field of
human rights, Dawit said, adding that China's experience in
economic development, poverty eradication and promotion of
development right is very important to Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Zeng noted that both China and Ethiopia are faced with the
task of economic development, tackling poverty, raising people's
living standard and improving rights of survival and development.
</P>
<P>
The two countries can learn from each other and draw lessons
from each other's experience, he said.
</P>
<P>
Since the two countries forged diplomatic relations in 1970,
bilateral cooperation in many fields have been very fruitful, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Zeng expressed China's appreciation with the support extended
by the Ethiopian government on human rights. He also expressed
the hope that the two countries' parliaments will strengthen
contact and cooperation in the future so that the overall
Sino-Ethiopian ties will be further developed. 
</P>
