<HEADLINE> U.S., Israel Pose Threats to Iran: Senior Officer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Commander of the Iranian Islamic
Revolutionary Guards Corps (IRGC) Rahim Safavi on Saturday
maintained that the United States and Israel are the major threats
to Iran.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a geography seminar in Imam Hussein University,
Safavi said that at present none of Iran's neighbors could pose
military threats to it and that Iran regards the U.S. and Israel
as the only threats, the conservative evening newspaper Kayhan
reported.
</P>
<P>
He said the allegations of the U.S. and Israel that Iran
damages peace and security in the Middle East is mere propaganda
campaign aimed at terrifying the regional countries and isolating
Iran.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that his country is adopting a foreign policy that
seeks unity of the regional countries and that it has taken
effective steps in this regard.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. accuses Iran of trying to undermine the Mideast peace
process, seek weapons of mass destruction and support terrorism.
</P>
<P>
The commander said that Iran can, instead, play a key role
in maintaining peace and security in neighboring areas, including
Persian Gulf, Gulf of Oman, Indian Ocean, Caspian Sea and Central
Asia.
</P>
<P>
Referring to Iran's safety, Safavi expressed confidence that
his country can guarantee national security in the coming years
since it enjoys strong cultural power, influence in the Islamic
world and internal stability.
</P>
<P>
However, he criticized the decisions on the country's
administrative divisions, saying they are not successful in view
of national interests and security.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Iran decided to divide some big provinces, including
the biggest northeastern province of Khorasan, bringing the number
of the administrative areas from 25 to 28. 
</P>
