of stamp collection is given much attention, it can be a useful
tool for the promotion of culture and education, local reports
said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Stamps can also play a role in attracting foreigners to visit
Tanzania, thus boosting the country's tourism industry, he said.
</P>
<P>
In a move to promote the philatelic business, the TPC chief
pledged to improve marketing and advertisement of new stamp
issues through mass media both at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The TPC director general urged the stamp collectors to form
clubs in their respective areas to develop the philatelic
business in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting, Jaffer Rawji, a well-known Tanzanian
philatelist, said it is discouraging to note that Tanzania with
less than 300 philatelist kids was doing very little in promoting
stamp collection business.
</P>
<P>
Rawji, who started collecting stamps since early 1970s, said
school children, overpowered by television and computers
nowadays, have grown less interested in stamps.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, which was attended by more than 50
philatelists including pupils, David Mdundom was elected as the
first interim chairman of the Stamp Collection Club.
</P>
<P>
TPC also stressed the need to promote stamp designing by
utilizing qualified Tanzanian artists and hold stamp shows at
trade fairs and international conferences. 
