<HEADLINE> New Government Formed in Yemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Yemen's new Prime Minister
Abdul-Karim al-Iryani appointed the 29 cabinet ministers on
Saturday, the Yemeni News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Al-Iryani, foreign minister in his predecessor's cabinet, kept
most of the members of the former government. There are three new
faces in his cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Abdul-Kader Abu-Gamal was named deputy prime minister and
foreign minister. His post in the Planning and Development
Ministry is succeeded by Ahmed Mohammed Sofan, ex-minister of
industry.
</P>
<P>
The key ministers of oil, finance and interior kept their posts.
</P>
<P>
Ex-minister of supply and trade Abdul-Rahman Mohammed Ali
Othman became minister of industry, and ex-minister of state for
cabinet affairs Ahmed Ali El-Beshari was appointed minister of
expatriate affairs.
</P>
<P>
The three new ministers are Minister of Supply and Trade
Abdul-Aziz El-Kamim and two ministers of state. 
