<HEADLINE> Defending Champion Dalian Wanda Suffers Second Defeat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Dalian Wanda
suffered its second defeat this season after being stunned by host
Yanbian Aodong 1-0 in the 11th round of the Chinese professional
soccer league on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Aodong, who stood ninth after the 10th round, went ahead 25
minutes into action when Park Soon-Bae opened the scoring on a
free kick.
</P>
<P>
Wanda geared up offensively but their efforts turned out
fruitless thanks to Aodong goalie Mukweyanzo Bulaylma's brilliant
performance.
</P>
<P>
Both sides failed to score in a rain-soaked second half.
</P>
<P>
In Shijiazhuang, Chinese Army was held to a 2-2 draw by the
visiting Wuhan Hongjinlong (previously named Wuhan Yaqi) 2-2.
</P>
<P>
The army team pulled ahead in the ninth minute with a goal from
Tao Peng.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Bo equalized the score 10 minutes later on a goalmouth
melee. Cai Sheng put the visitors ahead in the 29th minute with a
long shot.
</P>
<P>
Gu Chuan saved the army squad from a defeat by heading an
equalizer into the net In the 76th minute.
</P>
<P>
In the other games, the injury-jinxed Shanghai Shenhua,
runners-up last season, scored a hard win over Shandong Luneng
2-1; Shenyang Haishi drew with Guangzhou Apollo 0-0; Guangzhou
Songri ousted Sichuan Quanxing 1-0; Vanguards Huandao tied Beijing
Guo'an 0-0; Shen Zhen Pingan defeated Qingdao Hainiu 2-1. 
