<HEADLINE> CPPCC to Play More Active Role In Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, May 17 (Xinhua) -- The regional committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) of the Tibet
Autonomous Region should play a more active role in the region's
reform and development drive, said the committee's newly elected
chairman today.
</P>
<P>
Pagbalha Geleg Namgyai, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee
of the National People's Congress and chairman of the regional
committee of the CPPCC of the Tibet Autonomous Region, made the
remark in a speech delivered at the first session of the seventh
CPPCC regional committee, which closed today.
</P>
<P>
He said that the work of the regional committee should serve
the region's overall development, and a stable and united social
environment is vital for realizing the region's cross-century
development goal.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC committees at all levels should play active roles in
the region's economic development, providing good advice and
suggestions for government work, he said, adding that these
organizations should also strengthen their role of democratic
supervision.
</P>
<P>
He urged the regional committee to join the government's
efforts to help the people get a clear view of the Dalai Lama, who
is the head of a political group seeking "Tibet independence" and
the source of Tibet's social turmoil.
</P>
<P>
The ten-day meeting elected the chairman, vice-chairmen,
secretary-general and standing committee members of the seventh
CPPCC regional committee of Tibet, with 301 motions submitted and
258 adopted. 
</P>
