<HEADLINE> Diseases Claim 69 Lives in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, May 17 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of various diseases
has claimed 69 lives since March across the Himalayan kingdom of
Nepal, the official RSS news agency said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-six have died of pneumonia in Humla district of
midwestern Nepal since March, while the death toll from typhoid,
gastroenteritis, fever and influenza that are spreading in various
areas of the country since April has reached 33, the RSS said,
citing figures from the Health Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The outbreak of pneumonia in Humla is attributed to pervasive
malnutrition, inadequate immunization facilities, lack of health
education and sanitation, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
The Himalayan district of Humla is suffering from poor harvest
caused by drought last year.
</P>
<P>
A medical team is working in Humla to control the disease, the
RSS said.
</P>
<P>
It added that health workers along with necessary medicine have
also been dispatched to other affected areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
