<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji on Laid-Off Workers (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Guaranteed basic living standards
and the re-employment of workers laid off from state-owned
enterprises are top-priority matters that have a bearing on the
overall situation of China's reform, development and stability.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made by Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji here
Saturday, at the closing session of a national conference on the
problems of workers laid off from state enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"Officials in various departments must attach great importance
to this work, and make intensified and concerted efforts to make
it a success," said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
The three-day conference was jointly convened by the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the State
Council, China's cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing, members of the Standing Committee
of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, attended the
closing session, which was presided over by Hu Jintao,
vice-president and also member of the Politburo Standing Committee
of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Attended by the governors of all provinces and the heads of
central government departments, the conference was aimed at finding
effective ways to ensure the basic living standards of workers
laid off by state enterprises and help them get new jobs as
soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
After hearing a keynote speech by President Jiang Zemin at the
opening session, the discussion focussed on a circular on the
guarantee of basic living standards and the re-employment of
laidoff workers. The circular is expected to be issued soon by the
central government.
</P>
<P>
The participants agreed that at present the Party and the state
should focus their attention on workers laid off by state
enterprises, because the workers in state enterprises have made
major contributions to China's economic development, reform and
opening-up, and to the growth of the state sector.
</P>
<P>
A satisfactory solution to this problem will also serve as a
precondition for achieving the Party Central Committee's goal of
completing the reform in most state-owned enterprises within the
next three years, they added.
</P>
<P>
They also suggested that the central government tighten its
macro control of layoff workers from state enterprises, to make
sure that they do not add too much pressure to the employment and
social security.
</P>
<P>
They also pointed out the importance of holding top Party and
government officers at all levels responsible for the welfare of
workers laid off by the state sector and seeking support from the
whole society in this regard.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji said the overall situation for China's
national economy has remained good since the beginning of this
year, and the country's development has been basically normal in
the past few months.
</P>
<P>
"Some problems have appeared, but they were not unexpected and
should be mainly attributed to the impact of the financial crisis
in Asia," he said.
</P>
<P>
In line with the needs of economic growth and restructuring, he
said, the central government has taken timely and necessary
measures to expand domestic demand and increase investment.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident that an economic growth of eight percent for
this year is absolutely attainable," said the premier.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
