<HEADLINE> Shenyang Adds Digit to Local Telephone Numbers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 17 (Xinhua) -- This capital of northeast China's
Liaoning Province added one more digit to local telephone numbers
today, making the city's telephone numbers eight-digit ones.
</P>
<P>
The digit "2" has been added in front of the original telephone
numbers which began with the digits two, three, four or five, and
the digit "8" has been added in front of those which began with
six, seven, eight or nine.
</P>
<P>
The total capacity of the city's switchboards has reached more
than 1.51 million lines, with 1.1 million telephone
subscribers. Thirty one out of each 100 of the city's households
now have their own telephones.
</P>
<P>
"The city's telecommunications bureau can provide all the
telephone services which are available in the advanced countries,"
said Shao Wenzhang, director of the city's telecommunications
bureau.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang is the seventh large city in China to expand local
telephone numbers to eight digits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
