<HEADLINE> PNA Accuses Israeli Troops of Shooting Marchers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, May 17 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) Sunday accused Israeli troops of firing live
bullets at Palestinian marchers on Thursday and killing at least
nine.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference held in Gaza, Director General of PNA
Ministry of Health Imad Tarawieh said that autopsy has shown that
the nine victims were killed with explosive bullets.
</P>
<P>
Israeli troops deliberately aimed at the upper body of the
Palestinians taking part in the march, he said.
</P>
<P>
The PNA and some Palestinian groups organized a "million people
march" in the West Bank and Gaza Strip to mark the 50th
anniversary of the Nakba, or catastrophe in Arabic, in which
millions of Palestinians were forced homeless due to the founding
of the state of Israel on May 14, 1948.
</P>
<P>
"There was a crime committed by Israeli forces while facing the
Palestinian peaceful marchers," PNA Minister of Planning and
International Cooperation Nabil Sha'ath said in Gaza on Sunday,
referring to the killings.
</P>
<P>
"I believe this issue (killing) is conducted due to orders
from higher levels ..., when they (Israeli troops) receive orders,
they open fire for the purpose of killing," Sha'ath said.
</P>
<P>
The march has showed the Palestinians are ready to express
their tragedies and rights through actions not only on the
negotiation table, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the PNA minister warned of a dangerous situation in
the Middle East if peace efforts fail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
