<HEADLINE> Han Xue, Chao Na Win Two Titles for Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAODING, North China, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Han Xue and Chao Na,
both from Beijing, split the spotlight on the third day of the
Chinese National Swimming Championships here on Sunday, winning
the 100 meters breaststroke and the 100m freestyle, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Han, 17, women's short-course 50m breaststroke world record
holder, led the field at the 50m turn by a body-length but was
chased closely on the last 15 meters. She finally clinched the
title in a time of one minute 10.37 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Li Wei, from Shanghai, surged from the last 50 meters and
finished second in 1:10.86, ahead of Xu Shan in 1:11.10.
</P>
<P>
"I'm glad to win the gold, though the result is a little bit
slower than that at the Chinese National Games last October," Han
said. "I felt tired after the semi-finals."
</P>
<P>
"I should have swam 200m individual medley and 100m freestyle,
but the two events clashed with my speciality 100m breaststroke,
so I had to give up those two," Han added.
</P>
<P>
Chao Na, 18, who dominated the first 75 meters, held off the
strong challenge from her closest rival Nian Yun of Jiangsu
Privince to grab the 100m freestyle by one hundredth of a second
in 56.14.
</P>
<P>
World 400m individual medley world record holder Chen Yan came
into the third place in 57.00.
</P>
<P>
"Chao's personal best is 55.35, so her performance today
reflects her weakness in endurance, since she had already swam the
100m freestyle for five times, including 4X100m free relay and
preliminaries and semi-finals," Chao's coach Chen Yinghong was not
in a celebration mood.
</P>
<P>
Pan Licong from Heilongjiang Province won the men's 200m
butterfly in 2:02.08, Xie Xufeng won the silver in 2:02.17 and
Zhang Peng took the bronze in 2:02.77.
</P>
<P>
Wang Wei wrapped up his second gold medals in the men's 200m
individual medley in 2:05.52. Wang Xianqiang and Wang Haizhou
shared the second place with an identical time of 2:07.17. 
</P>
</TEXT>
