<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "People's Daily" Editorial on China's Re-employment Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- An editorial to be published in
tomorrow's "People's Daily" calls the guaranteeing of the basic
livelihoods and re-employment of laid-off workers important tasks
and major issues affecting the overall situation in China.
</P>
<P>
A proper settlement of these matters is not only vital for
state-owned enterprises to fulfill their reform programs and get
out of difficulties over the next three years, but will also have
a significant and far-reaching effect on the sustainable
development of the national economy, it says.
</P>
<P>
At a work conference held by the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China and the State Council, participants
studied the current economic situation of the country and overall
arrangements made to guarantee the basic livelihoods and
re-employment of laid-off workers, says the editorial, calling on
the whole nation to earnestly study and carry out the guideline
announced at the conference.
</P>
<P>
The editorial notes that it is inevitable that some workers
will be laid off and face re-employment in the course of the
transformation from the planned economy to the socialist market
economy.
</P>
<P>
This is a basic measure to reinvigorate the state-owned
enterprises by means of "encouraging mergers, regulating
bankruptcy, reducing the workforce and increasing efficiency and
carrying out reemployment program," it says.
</P>
<P>
The layoffs and re-employment have caused temporary
difficulties for some workers, the editorial says, but they are
conducive to economic growth and all-round social development, and
will finally create more favorable conditions for all the people
to become well-off.
</P>
<P>
With the support and firm leadership of the CPC Central
Committee and the State Council, the Party committees and
governments at each level have worked hard and made certain
achievements in handling the re-employment program, the editorial
says.
</P>
<P>
But the resolution of the issues of guaranteeing the basic
livelihoods and re-employment of laid-off workers are still hard
tasks and require further unifying thinking and extra work, it
notes.
</P>
<P>
The editorial emphasizes that the concerned departments must
work out feasible plans to make sure that the work will be
conducted in an organized and planned manner.
</P>
<P>
The Party committees and governments at each level must help
laid-off workers in fostering new employment concept in line with
the socialist market economy and offer them fine employment
services, while all social organizations must give more support
and create a sound social environment for laid-off workers, it
stresses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
