<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980517.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Arrives In Rome </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, Chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), arrived here on Sunday, starting his four-day
official visit to Italy.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese and Italian peoples have enjoyed a long history of
friendship, and the bilateral relations have gained smooth
development since the two countries forged diplomatic relations 28
years ago, especially in recent years with the joint efforts of
the two sides, our relations have scored fruitful achievements in
various fields," Li said in an airport address released upon his
arrival.
</P>
<P>
He said consolidating and strengthening the long-term and
stable cooperative relations oriented toward the 21st century not
only conform to the fundamental interests and common aspirations
of the two countries and peoples but also contribute to the world
peace, stability and development.
</P>
<P>
Li said he is looking forward to exchanging views with Italian
leaders on issues of common concern and that he hopes his visit
will help deepen the understanding and cooperation between the
CPPCC and Italian parliament and open new channels and forms of
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said he believes that his visit will reach the goal of
deepening understanding, broadening common ground, enhancing
friendship and expanding cooperation between the two countries, Li
said.
</P>
<P>
Li arrived here after concluding an official visit to
Romania. His four-nation Europe tour will also take him to Spain
and France. 
