<HEADLINE> 2 Palestinians Wounded as Clashes Continue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, May 17 (Xinhua) - Two Palestinians were reportedly
injured in the West Bank town of Hebron Sunday as clashes between
the Palestinians and Israeli soldiers entered its fourth day.
</P>
<P>
The Clashes erupted when Palestinians threw firebombs and
stones at Israeli soldiers, who responded with rubber bullets,
Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Israeli army banned Israelis from entering the West
Bank towns of Nablus, Ramallah, Bethlehem and
Palestinian-controlled part of Hebron, citing security reasons.
</P>
<P>
The Clashes between the Palestinians and Israeli soldiers
started with Thursday's "Million-Man March" staged by
Palestinians to mark the 50th anniversary of "al nakba."
</P>
<P>
Al nakba, Arabic for the "catastrophe," refers to the loss of
Palestinian homeland following the creation of Israel in 1948.
</P>
<P>
Eight Palestinians were reportedly killed and hundreds of
others wounded when the march on Thursday turned violent.
</P>
<P>
The latest wave of violence, the worst since September 1996,
broke out at a time when the Israeli-Palestinian peace talks were
stranded due to Israel's intransigent policies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
