<HEADLINE> Petrochemical Firm to Invest More to Expand Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Petrochemical Co. Ltd
plans to invest ten billion yuan (1.2 billion US dollars) to
expand its production capacity from last year through the years to
the year 2001, said an senior official from the firm.
</P>
<P>
By then, the firm's oil refining capacity is expected to reach
10 million tons, double the current level and that of ethylene
increase to 850,000 tons from present 550,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Most of the investment will be financed through banks, said Lu
Yiping, manager of the firm, recently, adding that an investment
of two billion yuan (241 million US dollars) last year has been
completed smoothly.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's petrochemical firms still have room for
development, as 30 to 40 percent of the petrochemical goods needed
for domestic use are imported. However, he added, the crucial
factor is to make our products more competitive on the world
market, and the technical upgrading will be given priority in the
expansion process.
</P>
<P>
The firm has also set its plan for the year 2010 in an effort
to quadruple its current total assets and sales volume.  
</P>
</TEXT>
