<HEADLINE> Ramos Condemns India's Nuclear Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 17 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines joins the world-wide
condemnation of India's two more nuclear tests on May 13 following
the three tests that were carried out on May 11, said President
Fidel Ramos.
</P>
<P>
In a statement published here Sunday, Ramos said that he is
"deeply disturbed over India's defiance of the strong support of
the international community for nuclear non-proliferation and
nuclear disarmament.
</P>
<P>
"I am also concerned at the effects of these tests on the peace
and stability in South Asia and at their serious implications for
global security," he added.
</P>
<P>
He strongly urged India to refrain from carrying out any
further tests and not to proceed with its nuclear program.
</P>
<P>
"I join the call of the international community in its appeal
for the neighbors of India to exercise the highest degree of
restraint in order to maintain peace and stability in the region,"
Ramos said.
</P>
<P>
He said that a nuclear arms race and nuclear proliferation
constitute a threat to international peace and security. 
</P>
