<HEADLINE> Anti-Corruption Officers Arrested in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Two Anti-Corruption Commission
(ACC) officers have been arrested for alleged demanding kickbacks
from a Lusaka business woman to save her from prosecution as an
exchange.
</P>
<P>
The two officers had been pressuring the woman to pay three
million Kwacha (about 1,500 U.S. Dollars) for them to close an
old case of alleged bribery which they accused her of being
involved in, Sunday Times of Zambia reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The woman, Nora Millies Madden, Director of Seekers Estate
Agents and General Dealer said Saturday that one of the two was
arrested when he went to her office Saturday afternoon to collect
a balance of 100,000 Kwacha, unknowing that other officers had
waylaid him after she tipped them.
</P>
<P>
The other man who had remained outside was also arrested and
they were taken to the commission's headquarters in Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
She said she was only saved from the harassment by the two men
after she reported the matter to one of the senior officer at ACC
last week.
</P>
<P>
she said she has given them more than one million Kwacha since
April this year when the problem began, adding that she could not
report the matter at first because she was scared.
</P>
<P>
"I was really scared and did not know where to report
especially that those troubling me were from the ACC until when I
was advised to report to their superiors," Madden said. 
</P>
