<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Eyes Health of Foreign-Invested Businesses  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- China will take to heart the
conduct of foreign-invested businesses and create a still better
investment climate so as to draw more overseas capital, said Shi
Guangsheng, minister of foreign trade and economic cooperation
(MOFTEC).
</P>
<P>
China will make full use of the existing laws and policies
concerning the use of capital from overseas to promote the healthy
growth of existing foreign-funded businesses, Shi said during a
recent interview.
</P>
<P>
He said this would set an effective example for potential
investment.
</P>
<P>
China will provide credit to ventures in accordance with the
credit principle, and is ready to help in time of need, he said.
</P>
<P>
While joint ventures are increasing capital or expanding stock,
the Chinese side often finds their proportion of stocks
decreased. China will help Chinese investors make effective use of
the capital market for financing in various ways. They may
restructure state-owned capital, issue shares and securities or
establish an investment fund, he said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, still greater efforts will be made to further
improve the investment environment, both the hardware and software.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, China will enhance infrastructure construction such
as energy, transportation, communications and other civil works
and, however, the software is more important, he noted.
</P>
<P>
First, all sorts of illegal examinations, charges,
apportionments, or fines should be resolutely stopped, he
said. The current charges should be put in order and, on the basis
of that, the charging units should report their work to
supervisors. In this way, legal charges will be protected
according to law wheareas illegal acts could be refused by
enterprises, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980517.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Eyes Health of Foreign-Invested Businesses (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Second, China should allow overseas-funded businesses to
operate on their own rights and guarantee that the legal interests
of all invested parties are not violated, as well as the proper
rights of the laborers.
</P>
<P>
Third, all government departments should accelerate their
efficiency, simplify administration, and make the public aware of
their rules and policies.
</P>
<P>
They should offer high quality, standardized and convenient
services for overseas objects.
</P>
<P>
By integrating with the deepened reforms in the investment and
circulation systems, they should improve the way to examine and
approve investments, and simplify the procedures.
</P>
<P>
The acts of all sorts of intermediary organizations should be
standardized, guided and supervised, he said.
</P>
<P>
Fourth, China will accelerated the building of an integrated,
open-market environment with order competition. Regional barriers
and departmental monopolies should be broken, and severe blows
should be dealt at the smuggling, counterfeiting and other illegal
acts.
</P>
<P>
Reform in the administration system of ports should be
stepped up, he said. Foreign-invested businesses also should
receive national treatment step by step.
</P>
<P>
Fifth, the assets of all relevant parties should be evaluated,
and foreign-funded businesses be examined on the implementation of
their contracts.
</P>
<P>
And China will carry out strict administration of taxation and
environmental supervision, and further improve the united annual
examinations of foreign-funded businesses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
