<HEADLINE> United States Draw 0-0 with Macedonia in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 16 (Xinhua) -- World Cup qualifiers the United
States were held to a disappointing goalless draw by Macedonia
Saturday in a soccer friendly at San Jose, California, on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The American team played the game without several key players
like midfielders Claudio Reyna, Ernie Stewart, Frnakie Hejduk and
Erie Wynalda and were thwarted by a tough Macedonian team which
failed to reach the finals in France.
</P>
<P>
The Americans did had some scoring chances but striker Brian
McBride squandered four clear chances. Cobi Jones twice narrowly
missed with a flick over the bar and a shot cleared off the line
by midfielder Toni Micevski.
</P>
<P>
Joe-Max Moore nearly scored in the final minute when he lunged
at a loose ball to push it past Macedonian goalkeeper Petar
Milosevski but the ball just rolled along the goalline and past
the post. 
</P>
