<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Introduce Investment from Multinational Companies (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- China welcomes investment from
multinational companies and will take bold steps to guide their
investment, said Shi Guangsheng, minister of foreign trade and
economic cooperation (MOFTEC).
</P>
<P>
China will continue to implement a policy of "market for
technology" and further open the domestic market, Shi said in a
recent interview.
</P>
<P>
By working in cooperation with multinational firms, he said,
China may introduce their advanced technologies, capital,
managerial experience and ways of marketing that are appropriate
for itself, and may enter their international network of
production, sales and service.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China will increase cooperation between the large
state-run enterprises and multinational companies, and promote the
newly-emerging industries and backbone industries, he acknowledged.
</P>
<P>
The government encourages businesses to set up
research-and-development centers with multinational companies,
which will help digest absorbed technologies and create new ones,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, China will further promote synchronized cooperation
between domestic businesses and multinational companies, and bring
along the growth of relevant businesses and industries.
</P>
<P>
China will also help large state-owned enterprises become
stronger and more competitive, he added.
</P>
<P>
Unified planning should be the first step for this kind of
cooperation, and appropriate measures should be taken, the trade
minister said. The cooperation should seek profits and refrain
from harms, and the state-owned economy should maintain its
dominant role in major industries and key areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980517.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Introduce Investment from Multinational Companies (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China will choose to protect some domestic infant industries
for a certain period of time from the impact of multinational
companies, a few of which might monopolize the market, illegally
transfer their revenues or evade taxes.
</P>
<P>
Another way of introducing capital from overseas is through the
international security market, Shi said.
</P>
<P>
Some large-and medium-sized state-run enterprises will be
selected, according to the national policies for industry and
utilization of foreign capital, to go public in the international
securities market, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, China will continue the experiment on a trial basis
of letting foreign-shared businesses go public abroad, and improve
the issue and exchange of stocks.
</P>
<P>
China will also seek the circulating means such as convertible
bonds, and further enhance cooperation and exchange with
international parties in the fields of security supervision and
operation. 
</P>
