<HEADLINE> 27 Killed in Natural Disasters in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Flood coupled with thunderbolt over
the past few days killed 27 people and injured 45 others in a
number of provinces of Iran, local daily Iran News reported on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Natural Disasters Headquarters at the Interior Ministry
announced on Saturday that flood caused by torrential rain killed
15 in northwestern province of East Azerbaijan, three in the
southwestern province of Lorestan, and one in the northern
province of Mazadaran.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, 35 others were injured and hospitalized in the three
provinces, the headquarters said, adding that all the
flood-stricken people have been offered temporary accommodation
and provided with basic and necessary goods.
</P>
<P>
During the past 48 hours, flood caused by heavy rainfall
claimed eight lives and injured 10 in the western province of
Chaharmahal-Bakhtiyari, it said.
</P>
<P>
It added that some 1,500 heads of livestock were rushed away by
the flood. 
</P>
