<HEADLINE> China to Optimize Foreign-Invested Industry Structure  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- China is set to adopt measures to
further optimize the structure of foreign-invested industry and to
attract overseas businesses to make investments in its central and
western regions.
</P>
<P>
Shi Guangsheng, minister of foreign trade and economic
cooperation (MOFTEC), made the remarks in a recent interview.
</P>
<P>
The State Council readjusted the tax policy on imported
equipment in December of 1997 and amended a guild list on
foreign-invested industry issued in 1995, he said. It is necessary
to carry out the newly approved guild list on foreign-invested
industry by the State Council in a comprehensive way.
</P>
<P>
He said that China will readjust the guild list when necessary
according to its economic development.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to carry out the notice on tax policy
readjustment on imported equipment issued by the State Council,
and to exempt from Customs duty and import value-added tax on
equipment and technologies used in foreign-invested projects that
China encourages and supports, he said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, he added, this practice applies to other
introduced advanced and suitable technologies.
</P>
<P>
Shi said that China encourages foreign businesses to invest in
export-oriented enterprises and carries out guaranteed account
system concerning the processing trade imports of raw materials
and parts and components.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he added, it is necessary to perfect the refund tax
system according to international practice and principle of
encouraging foreign-invested enterprises to purchase
domestically-made raw materials, and parts and accessories.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China will take the following measures to
encourage foreign businesses to invest in central and western
areas:
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980517.0142 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Optimize Foreign-Invested Industry Structure (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- Provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities can choose
industries and projects which have advantages to enjoy policies
concerning encouraged projects on the guild list with the approval
of the state.
</P>
<P>
With regard to the establishment conditions and market openness
concerning restricted projects or projects in which the ratio of
foreign shares are limited, it is necessary to ease restrictions
to some extent.
</P>
<P>
-- The state will arrange a host of projects in agriculture,
irrigation, transportation, energy, raw materials and
environmental protection in central and western areas for foreign
capital.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the state will give more support to project set
capital and relevant measures and support enterprises switched
from military to civilian purposes and large state-run enterprises
to use foreign funds for technological renovation.
</P>
<P>
-- It is necessary to encourage foreign-invested companies in
eastern areas to re-invest in central and western areas.
</P>
<P>
The project with foreign investment exceeding 25 percent of the
total can be treated as foreign-invested firms and receive due
preferential treatment.
</P>
<P>
-- Trial openness areas and projects allowed by the state
should proceed simultaneously in eastern, central and western
areas in principle.
</P>
<P>
With the approval of the state, provincial capitals can engage
in openness trials in the areas of domestic businesses, foreign
trade and tour agencies.
</P>
<P>
Shi said that central and western areas should improve their
investment environment, expand the introduction of foreign funds
and develop their respective economies according to their actual
conditions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
