<HEADLINE> Nicaragua Sets Record Coffee Production in 1997-98 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Nicaragua set a record of coffee
production in the 1997-98 period with 1.42 million bags in spite
of drought caused by the "El Nino" phenomenon, the Nicaraguan
Coffee Growers Union (Unicafe) announced.
</P>
<P>
Unicafe Executive President Amilcar Navarro said in Matagalpa
that the harvest was 220,000 bags more than the previous harvest
of 1.2 million.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the record harvest to the producers' efforts and
the coordination of the army and national police to reduce
vandalism, impunity and kidnapping.
</P>
<P>
Unicafe forecasts a 20 percent increase for the 1998-99 harvest
based on the areas cultivated. 
