<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Plans to Make Good Use of Foreign Investment: Trade Minister (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- China plans to absorb more overseas
investment, run foreign-funded firms better and further improve
the investment environment, according to Minister of Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC) Shi Guangsheng,.
</P>
<P>
It is essential to strictly control the scale of foreign debt
and maintain a sound structure, he said. It is essential to
reasonably define the scale and structure of foreign loans and
effectively control the amount of foreign debt according to the
demand of China's economic growth and condition, set, and the
repayment ability of its international balance of payments to
maintain its major foreign debt index above a secure line.
</P>
<P>
Noting that China will continue borrowing preferential loans
from international financial institutions and foreign governments,
He said his country will borrow long-term foreign export credit in
a moderate way and issue bonds overseas.
</P>
<P>
China will strictly control the use of other foreign business
loans and short-term liability, he said, adding that it is
necessary to regulate and enforce the unified supervision on the
amount and structure of foreign debt to guard against and cope
with the risk of finance and foreign debt in a practical manner.
</P>
<P>
And it is necessary to improve and regulate the management
of foreign debt, Shi said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said, it is necessary to better coordinate and
manage foreign loans and strictly censor and clean up the
department which makes foreign loans.
</P>
<P>
The preferential loans from international financial
institutions and foreign governments should be borrowed by
authorized sectors and re-loaned by designated organizations, Shi
said.
</P>
<P>
It is also necessary to formulate regular measures to re-loan
as quickly as possible, which will clearly define both rights and
responsibilities, he said.
</P>
<P>
The financial organizations which have the right to raise
business funds from overseas can do their job according to the
debt index, he said, and that large enterprises which are
qualified can borrow overseas directly with the approval of the
state.
</P>
<P>
He added that foreign-invested enterprises can borrow upon
their own decisions.
</P>
<P>
It is imperative to strictly ban illegal fund-raising and
floating loans under various pretexts overseas, Minister Shi said,
and that it is necessary to clear up hidden debt and invisible
foreign debt, and to severely penalize those violating regulations.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980517.0148 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Plans to Make Good Use of Foreign Loans: Trade Minister (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shi urged that great efforts should be made to improve the
efficiency of the use of foreign loans. Mid- and long-term foreign
loans should be used in infrastructure and development-oriented
projects, he noted, and preferential loans from international
financial institutions and foreign governments should be centered
on agriculture, irrigation, transportation, energy, environmental
protection and urban infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that it is imperative to raise the ratio of
those loans to the central and western areas.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, mid- and long-term loans to foreign businesses
should focus on basic, pillar and high-tech industries as well as
export-oriented projects in terms of introducing necessary
technologies, equipment and row materials, he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that short-term foreign business loans must not be
used on long-term projects and fixed assets and other unsuitable
areas.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that it is necessary to improve the
management of foreign loans, make pre-preparation for projects,
better evaluate projects, optimize loan use, attach importance to
efficiency and repayment ability, fulfill domestic set conditions,
and carry out project legal person and capital fund systems.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to set up a mechanism for borrowing, use and
repayment which is unified by responsibilities, rights and
interests, he noted, adding that all departments and enterprises
should improve the awareness of repayments and fulfill repayment
responsibilities.
</P>
<P>
All sectors which bear repayment responsibilities should ensure
the repayment at maturity, he said, and that it is necessary to
speed up the formation of a mechanism for repayment and assurance
according to laws and market-economy principles.
</P>
<P>
The financial sectors which borrow foreign funds should have
adequate foreign reserves and ensure the fulfilment of loan
contracts so as to maintain China's reputation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the departments concerned should bear due foreign
debt assurance or repayment responsibilities for preferential
loans from international financial organizations and foreign
governments used in public interest projects, Shi said, and that
local governments should establish a repayment fund according to
regulations.
</P>
<P>
Relevant departments should also take effective measures to
deal with debt delay and liability, the trade minister said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980517.0149 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 499 Dead in Wake of Rioting in Jakarta, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 17 (Xinhua) -- The death toll of three-day rioting
in Jakarta, capital of Indonesia, topped 499 Saturday and police
have rounded up more than 1,000 alleged rioters, a military
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
AS of 7 p.m. Saturday night, the death toll was 499, including
those burned to death and those who tried to save themselves by
jumping from burning buildings, Armed Forces spokesman Brig. Gen.
Wahab Mokodongan said here Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian Armed Forces (ABRI) will continue to work hard
and is ready to try their best to restore security and peace, the
Jakarta Post daily Sunday quoted the spokesman as saying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Deputy Jakarta Governor for Development Affairs
Abdul Kahfi said 3,029 buildings, 950 cars and 513 motorcycles
were destroyed or damaged during the rioting.
</P>
<P>
Police said they had arrested 1,027 alleged looters, several of
those were students, from various places all over the city.
</P>
<P>
"They were caught red-handed looting," a police spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Jakarta Military Commander Maj. Gen. Sjafrie Sjamsoeddin said
Saturday that the situation was under control and called for
business to resume in the capital.
</P>
<P>
"ABRI guarantees security," Sjafrie said.
</P>
<P>
Troops patrolled the city streets in armored vehicles in an
obvious move to show they were serious in their threat to take
stern action against troublemakers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
