<HEADLINE> European Countries ask Thailand to Provide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Several European countries have
asked Thailand to provide assistance for their nationals who have
fled from the unrest Indonesia and are taking temporary refugees
in Thailand, according to Thai Foreign Ministry Spokesman Kobsak
Chutikul.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands had conferred with the Thai Foreign Ministry,
asking for assistance regarding visa requirements should the riots
in Indonesia escalate and their citizens need to stay more than 15
days in Thailand, Kobsak was quoted Sunday by the Nation newspaper
as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said the France, Germany and the United Kingdom had also
made similar requests.
</P>
<P>
Citizens from most European countries and the United States can
stay in Thailand for 15 days without visa.
</P>
<P>
Kobsak said special flight-clearance arrangements had also been
requested for chartered flights carrying their nationals out of
Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Chaos in Jakarta which have left more than 500 people dead have
forced many people to flee the country, and various embassies have
had to prepare evacuation plans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
