<HEADLINE> Brazilian President Resumes European Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President Fernando
Henrique Cardoso on Saturday left for Madrid for a week-long visit
to Spain, Switzerland, and Portugal.
</P>
<P>
Cardoso cut short his visit to Spain late last month and
returned home for the funeral of former president of Chamber of
Deputies Luiz Eduardo Magalhaes.
</P>
<P>
Cardoso is scheduled to meet King Juan Carlos of Spain on May
18, and also meet Spain's businessmen to encourage their
participation in the privatization of Brazil's state-owed
enterprises, especially in the telecommunications sector.
</P>
<P>
Trade volume between Brazil and Spain was 1.1 billion
U.S. dollars in 1995 but the figure doubled in two years. Only
after the United States, Spain is the second largest buyer of
Brazil's privatized state enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Cardoso will also go to Geneva, Switzerland, to attend the
celebration of the 50th anniversary of the General Agreement on
Tariffs and Trade (GATT) on May 19.
</P>
<P>
GATT, the predecessor of the World Trade Organization (WTO),
went into force on January 1, 1948.
</P>
<P>
Cardoso will also go to Portugal to take part in the
inauguration of Expo Lisboa 98 on May 20 and return home on May
23. 
</P>
</TEXT>
