<HEADLINE> More Dengue Cases Reported in Rio de Janeiro State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, May 16 (Xinhua) -- More than 4,000 new cases of
dengue were reported in the Brazilian state of Rio de Janeiro last
week, "O Estado de Sao Paulo" said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Among the cities in the state, Niteroi registered 1,288
cases, the highest number, followed by Angra dos Reis, with 1,086
and Rio de Janeiro, with 164, reported the Brazilian daily.
</P>
<P>
The whole Rio de Janeiro state has reported 23,861 dengue cases
since January 1 this year with 8,507 cases in the city of Rio de
Janiero alone.
</P>
<P>
Dengue is an infectious tropical disease transmitted by
mosquitoes and characterized by severe pains in the joints and
back, fever, and rash. 
</P>
