<HEADLINE> Bank Indonesia Announces to Resume Banking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Bank Indonesia, the central bank,
has announced all banking operations, including clearing, will
resume on Monday (may 18), but observers say it will take weeks or
seven months for business to be back to normal.
</P>
<P>
No clearing took place on Thursday or Friday because of
wide-spread riots across Jakarta, capital of Indonesia, and most
of banks staffs were told to leave office, local leading
newspapers reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The three day riots has damaged many bank branches in shopping
centers.  
