<DOCNO> XIE19980517.0158 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Minister on the Use of Overseas Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- The overseas investment used by
China has been on steady rise and the level of overseas capital
utilization been improved during the past two decades thanks to
China's reform and opening-up policy, according to Shi Guangsheng,
minister of foreign trade and economic cooperation in a recent
interview.
</P>
<P>
Shi considered the capitals, either in form of direct
investment, foreign loans or funds raised through stock markets,
has partially fill the gap of capital shortage for his country's
massive construction.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China has adopted advanced and practical
technologies and managerial expertise, created more job
opportunities, earned taxes and hard currency, and expanded its
foreign trade by utilizing overseas investment, Shi said, adding
that all efforts combined improved the international
competitiveness of the country.
</P>
<P>
Shi went on to say that the move also played its role in
liberation of people's minds and the construction of the socialist
market-oriented economic system and relevant legal system.
</P>
<P>
The use of overseas capitals also enhanced economic ties
between the Mainland and Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan regions, thus
playing a positive role in Hong Kong's smooth return to the
motherland, the stable transition of Macao and the eventual
peaceful reunification of the whole China, Shi said.
</P>
<P>
"History has been and will continue to prove that the reform
and opening-up is the only road for China's modernization and
national rejuvenation," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Shi also enumerated some problems in this regard.
</P>
<P>
He said the overall investment structure is not well
planned. The technical level of some projects is low and some
sectors have seen repeated construction.
</P>
<P>
Certain departments and localities have implemented regulations
against the relevant state laws and regulations or approved
overseas-funded projects beyond their authorized powers.
</P>
<P>
A small number of departments overcharged foreign-funded
enterprises and conducted irrational check-up activities.
</P>
<P>
Some localities paid much attention to approval number of
enterprises but scant heed to the unsue management.
</P>
<P>
Some foreign-invested ventures violated Chinese laws and
regulations and caused damage of interests of the Chinese
partners.
</P>
<P>
And a some projects with low economic returns are incapable to
repaying the foreign loans.
</P>
<P>
Shi urged efforts to attach high importance to the existing
problems and find solutions to them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980517.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
