<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Diversify Channels on Use of Overseas Capitals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- China plans to adopt a new strategy
by diversifying the ways and means it uses overseas investment,
according to Shi Guangsheng, minister of foreign trade and
economic cooperation (MOFTEC) in a recent interview.
</P>
<P>
According to Shi, China will make greater efforts to attract
investors from North America, Japan and the European Union (EU)
and other developed nations and regions. Efforts will continue to
be made in drawing investment from the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR), Macao, Taiwan and Southeast Asian
countries.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, high-tech cooperation with Hong Kong SAR will be
further enhanced, he added.
</P>
<P>
China plans to adopt more investment absorption means accepted
by the international community, continue to allow the
establishment of foreign holding companies, approve foreign-funded
concession rights projects and projects that granted rights of
operation or rights of proceeds for foreign investors on a trial
basis.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China will continue to develop processing trade and
compensation trade by means of upgrading the existing projects and
improving their economic returns, he said. Guaranteed accounts for
importing material for the processing trade will continue to be
implemented.
</P>
<P>
According to Shi, large- and medium-size state enterprises are
being encouraged to use overseas capital in reorganizing assets,
giving play to idle assets and improving management.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded enterprises are encouraged to use China-made
equipment through the public bidding process.
</P>
<P>
Laws and regulations will be enacted for small state-owned
enterprises and collective enterprises to cooperate with, or sell
to, overseas investors, or form joint ventures.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he added, private businesses will be allowed to
absorb foreign capital.
</P>
<P>
China will also formulate trade promotion policies and improve
promotion methods by using modern electronic information
technologies, according to Shi.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
