<DOCNO> XIE19980517.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Improving Sentiment Lifts Chinese Stock Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Both Shanghai and Shenzhen markets
registered moderate gains last week as market sentiment improved.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai index finished at 1368.087, 10.492 points up from
the previous week's close. The Shenzhen index gained 25.12 points
to end at 4205.43.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai stock market suffered minor falls on Monday and
Tuesday, but rebounded strongly on Wednesday, pushing the index to
1369.26, the highest in recent months.
</P>
<P>
However, it turned out to be a brief recovery as the market
resumed a downward trend on Thursday, falling 2.135 points. It
gained a minor 0.96 points on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Weekly turnover was 46.87 billion yuan (5.65 billion US
dollars), up 12.9 percent from the previous week.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said companies with asset restructuring plans will
continue to be the leading market stars.
</P>
<P>
Last week, six listed companies, including five textile firms,
were approved by the China Securities Regulatory Commission to
suspend trading for one month for asset restructuring.
</P>
<P>
Investors and brokers hailed the move, regarding it a major
step towards stabilizing the market. In the past, speculation has
sent the prices of listed companies with asset restructuring
extremely high.
</P>
<P>
The hard currency B-share market experienced slack trading and
continuous falls in the first four days of the week, but rebounded
strongly on Friday since most investors expect the government to
take new measures to enliven B-share trading.
</P>
<P>
The B-share index finished at 50.616, 1.12 points up from the
previous week's close.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Shenzhen market reported a weekly turnover of
45.363 billion yuan (5.5 billion US dollars), virtually the same
amount as in the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The B-share market also rose on expectations of new policies to
boost the hard currency market, with the B-share index finishing
at 720.89, 78.19 points higher than the previous week.  
</P>
</TEXT>
