<HEADLINE> Jimenez Wins Fifth Stage of Tour of Asturias </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Jose Maria Jimenez of Spain won the
fifth and penultimate stage of the Tour of Asturias cycling race
and moved within 24 seconds of overall leader Laurent Jalabert of
France.
</P>
<P>
Jalabert crossed the finish line in fourth place in Saturday's
fifth stage, 11 seconds behind the front pack. But the result
still gave him a comfortable lead heading into Sunday's final
stage.
</P>
<P>
Mimenez covered the 193-kilometer fifth stage from Oviedo to
Alto del Acebo in 5 hours, 30 minutes and 52 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Rui Lavarinhas of Portugal and Santi Blanco of Spain finished
just behind Mimenez.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's final stage covers 160 kilometers from Cangas del
Narcea to Oviedo. 
</P>
