<DOCNO> XIE19980517.0177 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> News Analysis: Preparations for Clinton's Visit in Full Swing (1) by Peng Shujie, Liu Yunfei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton will
pay a state visit to China in late June, about five months ahead
of the original schedule. Chinese and U.S. officials are busy
preparing for this one-stop special visit to ensure its success.
</P>
<P>
President Clinton's China visit is in return for President
Jiang Zemin's U.S. trip in October and the first one by a
U.S. president in the past nine years. Clinton's visit is expected
to advance the bilateral relationship and add new vitality to a
constructive strategic partnership geared toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
A series of top U.S. officials have visited China in the past
five months to pave the way for the state visit, and to complete
the agreements made between Jiang and Clinton in Washington, D.C.
</P>
<P>
The list of recent visitors includes: Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright, Defense Secretary William Cohen, Acting Under
Secretary of State for Arms Control and International Security
Affairs John Holm, Under Secretary of State for Political Affairs
Thomas Pickering and Trade Representative Charlene Barshefsky.
</P>
<P>
Director of the General Logistics Department of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army Wang Ke and Vice-Foreign Minister Zhang
Deguang have also visited the United States.
</P>
<P>
As a result of these visits, an agreement to establish a
consultation mechanism to strengthen maritime military safety was
signed on January 19. Another one on setting up direct and secure
telephone links was signed on April 30. The U.S. government also
declared on March 19 that the United States will start nuclear
cooperation with China for peaceful purposes.
</P>
<P>
This cooperation between China and the United States has not
only provided continuous input for the bilateral relationship, but
it is also a harmonious prelude to Clinton's upcoming visit.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
