<HEADLINE> Costa Rican Exports Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rican exports grew 19.24
percent in the first quarter of this year against the same period
of 1997, the Foreign Trade Promoting Commission said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Goods exported during the first quarter amounted to 1.15
billion U.S. dollars, against the 967 million dollars registered
in the same period of last year..
</P>
<P>
Sales of industrial products amounted to 596 million dollars,
or 52 percent of the total exports, while agricultural goods were
worth 462 million dollars, or 40 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
The livestock and fishing sectors increased their sales by 32.3
percent to 92.3 million dollars in the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
The main destinations of Costa Rican exports are North America,
with 49 percent; the European Union with 25 percent, and Central
America with 13 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
