<HEADLINE> Fujian Province Standardizes Fees on Overseas Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 17 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province will
take further measures to standardize the collection of extra-tax
fees on overseas companies.
</P>
<P>
In the immediate pipeline is the publication of a booklet of
standard fees at the end of this month, according to a provincial
official.
</P>
<P>
Fujian canceled 56 administrative fees charged overseas firms
between January and mid-April, with more fee cancellations to be
announced soon.
</P>
<P>
In a recent decision on improving the investment environment,
Fujian declared that no more administrative fees will be imposed
on companies from overseas this year and next year.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the so-called overseas residents management fee and
several other charges will be suspended for two years, the
decision said.
</P>
<P>
An economically dynamic province on the east coast, Fujian has
a concentration of overseas-funded enterprises. Official figures
indicate that Fujian had approved 23,300 overseas-funded projects
by the end of March this year, with contracted and paid-in
investment hitting 50.8 billion and 22.8 billion U.S. dollars,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
More than 13,000 overseas-funded enterprises had opened for
business by the end of last year, with an annual output value
exceeding 100 billion yuan (12 billion US dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
