<HEADLINE> Garden Party Spreads Oceanic Knowledge Among Beijing Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 17 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 10,000 students from the
Chinese capital's primary and high schools took part in a garden
party on oceanic knowledge Saturday in Longtanhu (dragon pool)
Park.
</P>
<P>
The party, jointly sponsored by the State Oceanic
Administration and the Chinese Science and Technology Association,
was held to mark the "1998 Year of Ocean," which is expected to be
highlighted by a series of publicity activities across China.
</P>
<P>
The party consists of four parts: commemorative meeting of
"1998 Year of Ocean," publicity on oceanic knowledge, a painting
exhibition, and a demonstration of scientific experiments.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of children jointly painted a 100-meter-long scroll
with the theme of "Love Our Blue Sea." Model ship exhibitions also
were staged at the party.
</P>
<P>
The party will be followed by a series of publicity activities
aimed at enhancing the ocean awareness of the people across
China.  
