<HEADLINE> Veteran Boxer Mendy Wins WBA Lightweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 16 (Xinhua) -- Veteran boxer Jean-Baptiste Mendy of
France beat defending champion Ozubek Nazarov of Kyrgysztan and
won the World Boxing Association (WBA) lightweight title on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Mendy, 35, who narrowly beaten by compatriot Khalid Rahilou for
the WBA super-lightweight crown less than three months ago, kept
his opponent at bay throughout the bout with his long right
punches.
</P>
<P>
Mendy, who was also World Boxing Council (WBC) champion in the
category until last year, took advantage of his reach to prevent
the titleholder from boxing and take the upper hand of the bout.
It was his 61st bout in a long career of 15 years.
</P>
<P>
In another title fight on the same bill, Russian Anatoly
Alexandrov beat Frenchman Julien Lorcy for the World Boxing
Organization (WBO) super-featherweight title on a split 114-114,
116-113, 119-109 decision.
</P>
<P>
The title had been left vacant by Welshman Barry Jones after he
had been ruled out of boxing after a brain scanner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
