<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> G-8 Summit Issues Statement on Northern Ireland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BIRMINGHAM, May 16 (Xinhua) -- The Group of Eight (G-8) leaders
Saturday issued a special statement on Northern Ireland, calling
on all parties concerned in the Northern Ireland peace process to
work for a justified solution.
</P>
<P>
The G-8 leaders, who are attending their annual summit in
Birmingham, said in the statement that they "warmly welcome" the
Belfast Agreement on the future of Northern Ireland reached on
April 10.
</P>
<P>
"We commend all those involved in achieving an outcome which
reflects the fundamental aspirations of both parts of the
community in Northern Ireland," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
While acknowledging that the agreement presents challenges to
all parties, the G-8 leaders voiced their hope that it will
achieve "the widest possible support" not only as a basis for
political stability and peace, but also as an opportunity for
economic development and prosperity for all Northern Ireland
people.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the people in Northern Ireland and the
Republic of Ireland are due to hold a referendum on whether to
endorse the Belfast Agreement later this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
